Same problem here with tf 2.4.0 and the unconditional model provided in the README. I get a similar traceback for the conditional model: `TypeError: __init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'input_layers'`

I encountered a similar error, this time with PyTorch instead of TensorFlow.

Example snippet of my script:

```python
os.environ['VXM_BACKEND'] = 'pytorch'
import voxelmorph as vxm

pt_first_model = vxm.networks.VxmDense(
    inshape=[192, 256, 320],
    int_steps=5,
    int_downsize=2,
    unet_half_res=True,
    nb_unet_features=([256, 256, 256, 256], [256, 256, 256, 256, 256, 256])
)
```

Error:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "C:\Users\Joshua\AppData\Local\JetBrains\Toolbox\apps\PyCharm-P\ch-0\212.5457.59\plugins\python\helpers\pydev\pydevd.py", line 1483, in _exec
    pydev_imports.execfile(file, globals, locals)  # execute the script
  File "C:\Users\Joshua\AppData\Local\JetBrains\Toolbox\apps\PyCharm-P\ch-0\212.5457.59\plugins\python\helpers\pydev\_pydev_imps\_pydev_execfile.py", line 18, in execfile
    exec(compile(contents+"\n", file, 'exec'), glob, loc)
  File "C:/Users/Joshua/repos/spinalcordtoolbox/test-pytorch-model-issue.py", line 10, in <module>
    nb_unet_features=([256, 256, 256, 256], [256, 256, 256, 256, 256, 256])
  File "C:\Users\Joshua\repos\spinalcordtoolbox\venv_sct\lib\site-packages\voxelmorph\torch\modelio.py", line 34, in wrapper
    return func(self, *args, **kwargs)
TypeError: __init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'unet_half_res'
```

In my case, the problem is that:

* My model loading script relied on newer VoxelMorph features (`unet_half_res`) introduced in a Feb 1, 2021 commit (https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/commit/579a995492bddfe9ce38161e58cf260fc155c4fd). 
* However, I installed VoxelMorph from pip (`voxelmorph-0.1`), which was released on Sep 5, 2020.
* Version 0.1 does not have the `unet_half_res` argument.

To fix this issue:

* Don't install VoxelMorph from `pip`, or
* Limit your scripts to only using features included in `voxelmorph-0.1`, or
* Perhaps the VoxelMorph devs could release a new version on PyPI so that people who run `pip install voxelmorph` can access the newest changes to the model architectures. 

Thank you kindly! :)

issue.title: Integrate EvanBeal's contrast agnostic registration model into SCT's registration scripts

repository.name: spinalcordtoolbox
repository.description: Comprehensive and open-source library of analysis tools for MRI of the spinal cord.

license.name: GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0

issue.body:
This issue is for planning the integration of @EvanBeal's [contrast agnostic registration model project](https://github.com/ivadomed/multimodal-registration) into SCT's registration scripts.

### Proposed changes (copied from 2022-04-05 meeting minutes)

- Include preprocessing steps
- Load the models weights and build the architecture (using [VoxelMorph](https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph) functions)
- Use the models to produce the warping field
- Transform the warping field so it can be used with sct_apply_transfo
- Call this function from the [register function](https://github.com/spinalcordtoolbox/spinalcordtoolbox/blob/master/spinalcordtoolbox/scripts/sct_register_to_template.py#L1189) of `sct_register_to_template` 
    - And/or `sct_register_multimodal`? (TODO: Needs clarification)

### Remaining work

- [ ] Investigate if model can be converted to ONNX, or if we need to depend on VoxelMorph directly
   - NB: If it can't be converted, then SCT will have to depend on Tensorflow once more, which conflicts with the vision for #3735.

issue.title: Update PyPI Release
issue.body:
Hi there! @evanbeal has built a feature on your groundbreaking work for our [spinalcordtoolbox](https://github.com/spinalcordtoolbox/spinalcordtoolbox). We'd like to publish it as part of spinalcordtoolbox so our users can get better, but we've hit a [stumbling](https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/issues/228#issuecomment-1128034462) [block](https://github.com/spinalcordtoolbox/spinalcordtoolbox/issues/3760#issuecomment-1128045208), that the only version on PyPI is from 2 years ago:

[![pypi: voxelmorph](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/987487/168907686-0f28b3f4-f715-4c74-b336-1bac8711c598.png)](https://pypi.org/project/voxelmorph/#history)

Would you be willing to take some time to publish an updated release to PyPI so that we can build on it? We'd be really excited to turn this research into practical medical tools for our users.

Evan was able to build on voxelmorph by installing from your GitHub, but our users don't have that kind of training, so we need them to be able to use a standard package with standard dependencies.

body: Just an update on this - voxelmorph 0.2 has now been released on pypi. This version includes the unet_half_res argument from the development branch (among other changes 😃)
